        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 117 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Clarkesville, or near Tallulah Falls. This storm
was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tallulah Falls, Tallulah Gorge State Park, Lake Rabun, Hollywood, and
Turnerville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
